  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    
    <!-- Compelling Opening Story -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <span class="font-bold">December 3rd, 2024. 9:47 AM.</span>
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Sarah Chen, SEO Director at a Fortune 500 retailer, watched her traffic dashboard in disbelief. Organic search visits had dropped 34% in six weeks. Not from an algorithm update. Not from competitors. 
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Her customers hadn't stopped searching. They'd stopped <em>clicking</em>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
          ChatGPT was answering their questions directlyâ€”synthesizing information from her site, her competitors, and a thousand other sources into perfect, comprehensive responses. No links. No attribution. No traffic.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Sarah's experience isn't unique. It's the first tremor of a $1.2 trillion earthquake reshaping how humanity accesses information. And if you're still optimizing for the old system, you're about to become a digital archaeologistâ€”an expert in obsolete practices.
        </p>
      </div>
      
